## Figure Sizing

Here are some examples of changing the size of a figure.


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
plot(1:10)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](examples_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-1-1.png){fig-align='center' width=100}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
plot(1:10)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](examples_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-2-1.png){width=1600}
:::
:::


We can also specify `column: screen` and `out-width: 100%` so that the figure will fill the screen.
plot in the svg vector graphics file format.


::: {.cell .column-screen}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(pressure, aes(x = temperature, y = pressure)) + geom_point()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](examples_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.svg){width=100%}
:::
:::
